71//
72// Routines
73//
74int
75convert_dpme(DPME *data, int to_cpu_form)
76{
77#if BYTE_ORDER == LITTLE_ENDIAN
78 // Since we will toss the block if the signature doesn't match
79 // we don't need to check the signature down here.
80 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_signature);
81 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_reserved_1);
82 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_map_entries);
83 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_pblock_start);
84 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_pblocks);
85 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_lblock_start);
86 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_lblocks);
87 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_flags);
88 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_boot_block);
89 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_boot_bytes);
90 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_load_addr);
91 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_load_addr_2);
92 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_goto_addr);
93 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_goto_addr_2);
94 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->dpme_checksum);
95 convert_bzb((BZB *)data->dpme_bzb, to_cpu_form);
96#endif
97 return 0;
98}
99
100
101#if BYTE_ORDER == LITTLE_ENDIAN
102int
103convert_bzb(BZB *data, int to_cpu_form)
104{
105 // Since the data here varies according to the type of partition we
106 // do not want to convert willy-nilly. We use the flag to determine
107 // whether to check for the signature before or after we flip the bytes.
108 if (to_cpu_form) {
109 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->bzb_magic);
110 if (data->bzb_magic != BZBMAGIC) {
111 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->bzb_magic);
112 if (data->bzb_magic != BZBMAGIC) {
113 return 0;
114 }
115 }
116 } else {
117 if (data->bzb_magic != BZBMAGIC) {
118 return 0;
119 }
120 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->bzb_magic);
121 }
122 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->bzb_inode);
123 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->bzb_flags);
124 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->bzb_tmade);
125 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->bzb_tmount);
126 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->bzb_tumount);
127 return 0;
128}
129#endif
130
131
132int
133convert_block0(Block0 *data, int to_cpu_form)
134{
135#if BYTE_ORDER == LITTLE_ENDIAN
136 DDMap *m;
137 uint16_t count;
138 int i;
139
140 // Since this data is optional we do not want to convert willy-nilly.
141 // We use the flag to determine whether to check for the signature
142 // before or after we flip the bytes and to determine which form of
143 // the count to use.
144 if (to_cpu_form) {
145 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->sbSig);
146 if (data->sbSig != BLOCK0_SIGNATURE) {
147 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->sbSig);
148 if (data->sbSig != BLOCK0_SIGNATURE) {
149 return 0;
150 }
151 }
152 } else {
153 if (data->sbSig != BLOCK0_SIGNATURE) {
154 return 0;
155 }
156 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->sbSig);
157 }
158 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->sbBlkSize);
159 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->sbBlkCount);
160 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->sbDevType);
161 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->sbDevId);
162 reverse4((uint8_t *)&data->sbData);
163 if (to_cpu_form) {
164 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->sbDrvrCount);
165 count = data->sbDrvrCount;
166 } else {
167 count = data->sbDrvrCount;
168 reverse2((uint8_t *)&data->sbDrvrCount);
169 }
170
171 if (count > 0) {
172 m = (DDMap *) data->sbMap;
173 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
174 reverse4((uint8_t *)&m[i].ddBlock);
175 reverse2((uint8_t *)&m[i].ddSize);
176 reverse2((uint8_t *)&m[i].ddType);
177 }
178 }
179#endif
180 return 0;
181}
182
183
184void
185reverse2(uint8_t *bytes)
186{
187 uint8_t t;
188
189 t = *bytes;
190 *bytes = bytes[1];
191 bytes[1] = t;
192}
193
194
195void
196reverse4(uint8_t *bytes)
197{
198 uint8_t t;
199
200 t = *bytes;
201 *bytes = bytes[3];
202 bytes[3] = t;
203 t = bytes[1];
204 bytes[1] = bytes[2];
205 bytes[2] = t;
206}
